<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-02-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-02-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="353" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d353">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.51/489</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Admiral <persName type="from">Caperton</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of the Navy</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Port au Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-02-03">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 3, 1916</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Everything quiet. Haitian Government stated that military officials under
                            titles of Commandants of Arrondissements, Chiefs of Sections,
                            Commandants of Communes, have been discharged throughout Haiti. Military
                            and police functions will be carried on by gendarmerie. One hundred nine
                            detachments of constabulary occupying one hundred nine different
                            stations in Haiti. The country will be thoroughly patrolled and order
                            kept. Had conference with President and Government Ministers today on
                            various subjects. Attitude Haitian Government always cordial. It
                            expresses desire to carry out all wishes of United States.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">W. B. Caperton</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>